did.abstract: University of Washington student, President of International Longshoremen's and Warehousemen's Union, author, sociologist

bioghist.p: Filipino author, sociologist, labor union official. Rojo was a president of ILWU No. 7. He was a student at the University of Washington and at Stanford, where he was a research fellow.

scopecontent.p: Unpublished manuscripts of scholarship on labor and living conditions of Filipino American cannery workers and scholarship, poems, and articles related to various other aspects of the community and its history. Newspapers from the Phillipines and Filipino American community newspapers from Seattle, San Francisco, Los Angeles and Stockton.
